  <div class="xhr_comment_photo">
    	<a alt="Laura" href="/user/show/136968272-laura"><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1627449668p1/136968272.jpg" alt="136968272" /></a>
  </div>
  <div class="xhr_comment_body">
    <a style="font-weight:bold" href="/user/show/136968272-laura">Laura</a>

      
<span id="freeTextContainer14240460166162435387">I think the book was purposefully written that way. (Sentences that weren’t “colorful” and from Charlie’s point of view) it was somewhat like a diary </span>
  <span id="freeText14240460166162435387" style="display:none">I think the book was purposefully written that way. (Sentences that weren’t “colorful” and from Charlie’s point of view) it was somewhat like a diary after all. So that doesn’t mean the book is bad because of that</span>
  <a data-text-id="14240460166162435387" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

    <br/>

    <span class="xhrCommentFooter greyText">
      Jul 21, 2021 06:21AM
    </span>

